The paper deals with secure message transmission over networks, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of linear programming formulations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the network optimization (cs.NI) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the incorporation of different scenaria may make the paper relevant to the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
